#use wml::debian::template title="Applicant's Checklist"

<P>The information on this page, while public, will primarily
be of interest to Debian developers in future.</P>

<P>Current registration process of New Maintainers are handled
by the <A HREF="./newmaint#Commitee">NM-Committee</A>. Normally,
the process is started with a mail from an applicant sent to 
the <A HREF="./newmaint#FrontDesk">Front Desk</A> or the applicant
can apply directly through the
<A HREF="http://nm.debian.org/newnm.php">New Maintainer Application</A>
webpage interface.
Then an <A HREF="./newmaint#AppMan">Application Manager</A> is 
assigned for each applicant, to collect the required information for
registration and to form the final report.
Finally, the <A HREF="./newmaint#DAMan">Developer Accounts Managers</A>
judges the final report from the Application Manager, does additional
checks such as phone contact if required, and completes the process by
assigning accounts to the new maintainer.
</P>

